w for a Keplerian accretion disk. The phase of the flaring regions was\ncoincident with the inner spiral arm structure identified during the early\nsuperhump phase. Our disk wind model with the enhanced emission from the inner\narm structure successfully reproduced the observed properties of He II 4686\n\\AA. Therefore, V455 And is the first case in dwarf nova outbursts that the\npresence of the disk wind is inferred from an optical spectrum.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 22 Jan 2022 16:26:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-30"}
